 {"id":"bd-jl3i","title":"Extend CancelReason with attribution fields","description":"## Overview

Extend the CancelReason type to include detailed attribution: origin region, origin task, timestamp, message, and cause chain.

## Current State

Currently CancelReason is likely a simple enum:
```rust
pub enum CancelReason {
    User,
    Deadline,
    Parent,
}
```

## Target State

```rust
/// Detailed cancellation reason with full attribution.
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct CancelReason {
    /// Primary cause category.
    pub kind: CancelKind,

    /// Region that initiated cancellation.
    pub origin_region: RegionId,

    /// Task that initiated cancellation (if applicable).
    pub origin_task: Option<TaskId>,

    /// When cancellation was requested.
    pub timestamp: Instant,

    /// Optional human-readable description.
    pub message: Option<String>,

    /// Parent cause if propagated from another region.
    /// Forms a chain: child -> parent -> grandparent -> ...
    pub cause: Option<Box<CancelReason>>,
}

/// Cancellation cause categories.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub enum CancelKind {
    /// User explicitly called cancel().
    User,
    /// Deadline budget expired.
    Deadline,
    /// Poll quota budget exhausted.
    PollQuota,
    /// Cost budget exhausted.
    CostBudget,
    /// Parent region was cancelled (check cause for details).
    ParentCancelled,
    /// Runtime shutdown requested.
    Shutdown,
    /// Required resource became unavailable.
    ResourceUnavailable,
    /// Race combinator: another branch completed first.
    RaceLost,
}
```

## Helper Methods

```rust
impl CancelReason {
    /// Create a new cancellation reason.
    pub fn new(kind: CancelKind, origin_region: RegionId) -> Self;

    /// Add a message to this reason.
    pub fn with_message(self, msg: impl Into<String>) -> Self;

    /// Add origin task.
    pub fn with_task(self, task: TaskId) -> Self;

    /// Chain this reason to a parent cause.
    pub fn caused_by(self, parent: CancelReason) -> Self;

    /// Iterate through the cause chain.
    pub fn chain(&self) -> CancelChainIter<'_>;

    /// Find the root cause (bottom of chain).
    pub fn root_cause(&self) -> &CancelReason;

    /// Check if this cancellation was due to a specific kind.
    pub fn is_kind(&self, kind: CancelKind) -> bool;

    /// Check if any cause in the chain is a specific kind.
    pub fn any_cause_is(&self, kind: CancelKind) -> bool;
}
```

## Backwards Compatibility

Keep conversion from old enum:
```rust
impl From<OldCancelReason> for CancelReason { ... }
```

## Acceptance Criteria

